result.name: Hummingbird Coffee & Food

reviews.text:
Hidden in Cheung Sha Wan, Humming Bird Coffee and Food is a very homey restaurant with amazing bird-based decoration. I particularly adore this shelf with the shape of bird that is filled with retro objects which would bring back so many memories.

Each table is nicely decorated with beautiful cotton flower, which touched up the whole dining atmosphere so much. You never know a bit of props could give you so much joy!

I ordered this Beef Burger with Beetroot Sauce and Chips with a cup of Bailey’s Chocolate. 

The Bailey’s Chocolate was so smooth and rich, and the Bailey’s in it definitely topped up the whole drink to a really sassy and enjoyable drink for a Saturday night.

As for the burger and chips, they were simply fantastic! The beef was so meaty and delicious! Bun was toasted and had a crunchy top.I couldn’t quite taste the beetroot sauce though. Chips were ordinarily good.

Surprisingly, Humming Bird also serves a variety of beer. Definitely a great place for you to catch up with your friends, or just to chill out a bit.
A small cafe located in a quiet street. Nice food and a good environment for chatting. Will definitely revisit
Had lunch to celebrate birthday with my sister. Chill and comfortable environment. A bit pricey.

Quite costly choice in Sham shui Po district. 65 for a lunch set with a complimentary coffee. Food quality was so so. Appreciate the service of the waitress as she served coffee after meal (which was quite uncommon act in Hk if not specified).

went there for coffee only. strong flavour.
quite chill to sit outside.
service was very local style i.e. no response when you say “thank you”.

鹹魚肉餅漢堡幾特別，肉餅太乾而鹹魚味不夠。沙律感覺新鮮，炸雞和薯條處理得不錯，新鮮炸起一定好食。Latte奶泡很滑，份量不太夠。最後甜品香蕉有點少，麻糬窩夫味道不錯又飽肚。

由於是小店，所以上菜要等待一下。價錢不算貴，以這水準值得一試。
地方雖小 , 食物可以, 唯一不太方便是比較隔涉.
